OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 7 Jul to Thu 16 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure will dominate across
OL,7,FEngland and Wales into next week,
OL,8,Flikely extending its influence into
OL,9,Fthe northern UK with time. This will
OL,10,Fbring dry and warm conditions with
OL,11,Fplenty of sunshine for most. Scotland
OL,12,Fand Northern Ireland will probably see
OL,13,Fmore cloud at first, with periods of
OL,14,Frain at times. Through next week
OL,15,Fthough the high pressure may extend
OL,16,Fnorthwards to bring periods of drier
OL,17,Fand warmer weather to Scotland and
OL,18,FNorthern Ireland. Winds will be light
OL,19,Fto moderate for most, though stronger
OL,20,Faround northern hills and coasts near
OL,21,Flow pressure systems. Temperatures
OL,22,Fbecoming widely warm, perhaps locally
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fhot in parts of the southeast,
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Falthough not as hot nor humid as seen
OL,25,Fin the past week.
